== Basic Rwt Application

This is a basic Rwt Application to serve as a starting point or as an example
of how to include Rwt in an existing Rails application.

The following script should be followed to adapt an application to Rwt:

- Install the rwt_plugin (see http:// OR
    - copy (or link) the rwt/lib directory to the app/lib directory
    - copy (or link) the ExtJs library to the public/ext directory

- If you are not using the plugin, include the Rwt module in the application
  controller (/app/controllers/applicationl.rb):

    require 'rwt'  # <<--
    class ApplicationController < ActionController::Base
      include Rwt  # <<--
      helper :all
      protect_from_forgery
    end

- Create a controller to act as the main entry to the rwt application:
  (/app/controller/desktop_controller.rb):

    class DesktopController < ApplicationController
      def index
        respond_to do |format|
          format.html
          format.js {rwt_template}
        end
      end
    end

- Create the views associated with the desktop_controller 
  (/app/views/desktop/index.html.erb):

    <!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd">
    <html>
    <head>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
    <title>Basic Rwt Application</title>

    <!-- The ExtJs library -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/ext/resources/css/ext-all.css" />
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/ext/adapter/ext/ext-base.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/ext/ext-all.js"></script>


    <!-- Rwt application entry template -->
    <script src="/desktop/index.js" type="text/javascript"></script>

    </head>
    <body>
    </body>
    </html>

  (/app/views/desktop/index.rb):

    rwt_app do |app|
      app << toolbar do |tb|
        tb << menu('Test') do |m|
          m << menu_item('Basic CRUD',call_view('/crud/index'))
          m << menu_item('Other tests',Rwt.message('Other tests','To include other tests, alter the menu in /app/views/desktop/index.rb'))
        end
      end
    end

- Alter routes.rb redirecting the main entry of your application:
  (/config/routes.rb):

    ActionController::Routing::Routes.draw do |map|
      map.root :controller => "desktop", :action=>'index'

      map.connect ':controller/:action/:id'
      map.connect ':controller/:action.:format'   # <<-- INCLUDE THIS ROUTE TOO!
      map.connect ':controller/:action/:id.:format'
    end

- Delete the index.html file in the /public directory and run the application 
  (you should see a menu at the top of your page).

